INSERT INTO `positions` VALUES (1,'A woman\'s right to privacy supercedes the fetus\' right to life.','In relation to abortion, privacy is defined as the ability of a woman to decide what happens to her own body. In political terms, privacy can be understood as a condition in which one is not observed or disturbed by government. \r\n\r\nEileen L. McDonagh explains privacy in US law:\r\n\r\nAlthough not widely understood, there are in fact two components to the right to bodily integrity and liberty: the right of a person to choose how to live her own life and the right of a person to consent to the effects of a private party on her bodily integrity and liberty. In the context of constitutional guarantees, a person\'s right to consent to \"what is done\" to her body is an even stronger right than a person\'s right to choose \"what to do\" with her life...Since there are two components to the right to bodily integrity and liberty--choice and consent--once the state designates the fetus as an entity separate from the woman, her right to terminate pregnancy stems not only from her right to make a choice a',1,1),(2,'Abortion should be illegal because terminating the life of a fetus is immoral','',1,1),(3,'Utility-scale wind power should be subsidized by the federal government','',2,1),(4,'The Production Tax Credit should be extended for 10 years','',2,1),(6,'Sexual emancipation and gender equality justify abortion in all cases.','Women\'s freedoms are limited until they can have the right to abortion on demand and to walk away from parenthood like men can. Governments that ban abortion arguably burden women with certain duties that men (who, too, are responsible for the pregnancy) are not also held accountable to, therefore, creating a double standard. Margaret Sanger wrote: \"No woman can call herself free until she can choose consciously whether she will or will not be a mother.\" Denying the right to abortion can be construed from this perspective as a form of female oppression under a patriarchal system, perpetuating inequality between the sexes.',1,1),(7,'Global warming is a farce imposed by seekers of research funding','I choose to ignore science.',9,1),(10,'The federal government should make radical policy changes to try to avert disaster','Global warming is an issue that requires world cooperation to reduce greenhouse gas emissions, and each country\'s federal government should have as a high priority making the hard choices to avoid catastrophe. Even the optimistic scenarios for climate change paint a grim picture of mass species extinction, ecological shifts that will make it hard or impossible for people to live in certain parts of the world, and rising sea levels. This will inevitably lead to large-scale migrations of people and straining of the remaining habitable land. With these predicted outcomes, the federal government should be doing everything it can to steer us away from the cliff we are headed toward.',9,1),(13,'Tar sands oil production should be terminated','The environmental cost of producing this oil is too high. Local pollution, water use, and carbon emissions are all reasons that this form of fossil fuel energy production should be prevented. This prevention could be in the form of a carbon tax, or the energy company could be forced to restore the land and water to its original state, which would make the cost of producing it infeasibly high.',12,1),(29,'Global warming is happening, but we can only prepare for it','Might as well hunker down, stockpile and buy guns.',9,1),(30,'This is my position','adlfkjsdlkfjsaldkfj',16,1),(32,'This is another position','Here is my justification.',16,13),(31,'President Obama should reject the Keystone XL project','Climate change is upon us and we should be doing everything we can to reduce our greenhouse gas emissions in order to get back to 350 parts per million CO2 in the atmosphere. Tar sands oil requires additional processing that consumes considerably more energy to produce, making it a worse contributor to climate change. Stopping this pipeline would show the world that the US is committed to doing its part to reduce greenhouse gases, and it would make it slow the rate of exploitation of the tar sands region, and the consequent burning of those fossil fuels.',17,1);
/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `positions` ENABLE KEYS */;
